$ SQLcl: SET ENCODING
@ encoding

`set encoding` sets the → development/Unicode/character-encoding for the current session.
-
Apparently, in SQLcl, `set encoding` should be used because the value of → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/nls#ora-nls_lang[`nls_lang`] is not taken into account.

code {
SQL> set encoding ISO-8859-1
code }

sa:

  A list of possible values for `encoding` can be obtained with `set encodings`.

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/SQLcl/commands/set`
